## STRUCTURE

- Top of every PHP file: `defined( 'ABSPATH' ) || exit;`
- Namespace everything: `Acme\MyPlugin\…`. Use classmap autoload (not PSR-4) — WordPress requires `class-*.php` file naming which is incompatible with PSR-4's directory-mirrors-namespace convention
- Hooks register in `Plugin::register_hooks()` or per-feature `register()` methods — no scattered `add_action`
- One responsibility per file
- Never modify core, parent themes, or third-party plugins — extend via hooks
- Every user-facing string uses `__()` / `esc_html__()` / `_x()` with a LITERAL text-domain matching the plugin slug
- No dead code, no commented-out blocks, no `console.log` / `error_log` left in shipped code
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT

---

## TOOLING

- PHP: PHPCS with WordPress-VIP-Go + WordPress-Extra + WordPress-Docs. PHPStan with `szepeviktor/phpstan-wordpress` at level 8.
- Plugin JS (`admin/`): `@wordpress/scripts` (lint-js, lint-style, build, test-unit-js), `@wordpress/eslint-plugin`.
- Ware apps (`wares/*/`): Vite + React 19 + TypeScript strict. See `wares-react-css.mdc`.
- Pre-commit: Husky + lint-staged.

## VERIFICATION LOOP — run before declaring any task done

After ANY code change to the plugin, run in order and fix until green:

1. `php composer.phar lint` (phpcs + phpstan)
2. `npm run lint`
3. `npm run build`
4. `php composer.phar test` (if tests exist)
5. `npm test` (if tests exist)

For ware changes, run inside the ware directory: `npm run build` and `tsc --noEmit`.

"Done" means ALL of the above are green. Do not report success otherwise.

## WORKING STYLE

- Match existing code style. Run `composer format` / `npm run format`.
- Small, focused changes. If touching >6 files, propose a plan first.
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT.
- No dead code, no commented-out blocks, no `console.log` / `error_log` in shipped code.
- If something in this file seems wrong for the current project, say so and suggest an update.
